tablished version of events and told an unpalatable truth\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.marthagellhorn.com/previous.htm|title=Previous Winners|website=www.marthagellhorn.com}}</ref> \n* 2006: Foreign Press Association, London. Runner up British Media Award for Zimbabwe coverage\n* 2009: Foreign Press Association, Runner Up, Print/Web Feature Story of the Year for a series retracing route of \"Grapes of Wrath\" to report on economic depression in modern America\n\n==Works==\n* ''American Overdose: The Opioid Tragedy in Three Acts'', Public Affairs, 2018, {{ISBN|9781610398619}}. Shortlisted for the J. Anthony Lukas Book Prize 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://journalism.columbia.edu/2019-lukas-prize-shortlist|title=Columbia Journalism School Announces the 2019 J. Anthony Lukas Prize Project Awards Shortlist {{!}} School of Journalism|website=journalism.columbia.edu|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>. Longlisted for the 2019 Orwell Prize for Political Writing<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.orwellfoundation.com/the-orwell-foundation/news-events/news-events/news/orwell-prizes-2019-longlists-announced/|title=The Orwell Prizes 2019: Longlists announced|website=The Orwell Prize}}</ref>.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*{{C-SPAN|117619}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McGreal, Chris}}\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:The Guardian journalists]]\n[[Category:Criticism of journalism]]\n[[Category:Arab\u2013Israeli conflict]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_McGreal"}
